main event: Radar analysis of an unidentified object observed at Offutt AFB, Nebraska on October 12, 1953.
interesting points: The object was detected on ground radar, with its altitude varying between 25,000 to 37,000 feet.
The object was moving with the wind at the levels where wind was reported.
The report includes multiple sightings of unidentified objects on different dates in October 1953.
One object was described as disc-shaped and flying at speeds between 200-700 miles per hour, with altitude varying between 25,000 to 57,000 feet.
The objects were observed by both military personnel and civilian witnesses, who were regarded as highly competent and reliable.
sighted object: disc-shaped and other unidentified objects detected on radar
